-- NZ's Heartland year profit rises 
-- 
-- Sun Aug 24, 2014 05:51PM EDT
-- None



WELLINGTON, Aug 25 (Reuters) - New Zealand bank and financial services company Heartland Ltd <HNZ.NZ> posted an annual profit in line with expectations as its income improved in the strongly growing economy.

The company reported an after tax profit for the 12 months to June 30 of NZ$36 million ($30.03 million) against the previous year's NZ$6.9 million. It had forecast a profit of about NZ$36 million.